{
  "texts": [
    "The accuracy attained for identifying people with MCI by the model is 80.9%.",
    "These findings show that brain morphology research gives an excellent method for non-invasive, objective evaluation, clinical, and early detection of AD.",
    "Despite the ADNI database's abundance of MCI samples, clinically identifying MCI patients is difficult.",
    "Further, Liu et al. (2022) devised a technique utilizing 3D DCNN to precisely differentiate patients with mild AD dementia from those with MCI and CN using sMRI.",
    "A reference model is constructed through the dimensions and thickness already known regions of brain that affected from the disease."
  ]
}